{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2ab83aab-394b-453a-a2a5-33cebb896987","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2 / .NET 9** — here's the modern recommended pattern:\n\n**Constructor injection** for `TestContext`, sync init in the constructor, and async init via `[TestInitialize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service;\n\n    // Sync init + TestContext injection via constructor\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        _service = new MyService();\n    }\n\n    // Async init runs before each test\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        await _service.ConnectAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void SyncTest()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_testContext);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points (MSTest v3+):**\n- `TestContext` is injected via **constructor** — no need for the legacy `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern.\n- `[TestInitialize]` supports **`async Task`** return type natively.\n- Put sync setup in the **constructor**, async setup in **`[TestInitialize]`**.\n- For class-level async init, use `[ClassInitialize]` (must be `static`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"af4dadf6-f90a-4f46-bf84-dd6e71d31890","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9. Let me provide the modern recommended approach.\n\nIn MSTest v3, the recommended way to:\n1. Inject `TestContext` is via constructor injection (the `TestContext` property setter pattern still works but constructor injection is the modern way)\n2. For sync initialization: use `[TestInitialize]` method or constructor\n3. For async initialization: use `[TestInitialize]` with an async method (MSTest v3 supports async `TestInitialize`)\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully for MSTest 3.x:\n\n- `TestContext` can be injected via constructor (MSTest v3+) or via the classic property pattern\n\n\n- Class-level setup and teardown use `[ClassInitialize]` and `[ClassCleanup]`, while per-test setup and teardown use `[TestInitialize]` and `[TestCleanup]`\n- MSTest v3 lets you make `[TestInitialize]` and `[TestCleanup]` async by returning `Task`\n- You can combine constructor injection for sync setup with an async `[TestInitialize]` method for more complex async operations\n\nLet me put together a clear example.","outputTokens":655,"requestId":"1040:2461FB:38D17BF:3E914D9:6A02ED02"},"id":"2bb76d26-fef2-4a3c-9d27-8e9f706f7a0f","timestamp":"2026-05-12T09:04:21.536Z","parentId":"4d93dd0d-0606-4b68-899d-b4450af9f748"}
